{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_24","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-liquibase:4.1.0`. Preserved work is available on branch https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-8466-library-new-request-org.springframework.boot-spring-boot-liquibase-4.1.0-c3aa2614. Metrics also ended in failure after 5 iterations of `dynamic_access_main_sources_pi_gpt-5.5` with 304 LOC generated, and dynamic-access coverage is unavailable (`stats/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-liquibase/4.1.0/execution-metrics.json`).\n\nThe most likely failing stage is the post-generation metadata-fix/native-test loop. The first native failures came from generated tests that write Liquibase XML changelogs with `http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog/dbchangelog-latest.xsd`; native image rejected that with “Accessing a URL protocol that was not enabled” in `logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-liquibase:4.1.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-26T22-07-22-710159Z.log`. After those tests were removed, the final rerun still failed in `:nativeTest` for the two auto-configuration tests with `BeanDefinitionStoreException` while processing `LiquibaseAutoConfiguration$LiquibaseConfiguration`, caused by missing `org/springframework/boot/context/properties/EnableConfigurationPropertiesRegistrar.class` in `logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-liquibase:4.1.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-26T22-31-54-851121Z.log`. `logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-liquibase:4.1.0/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows repeated metadata-fix attempts around `LiquibaseAutoConfiguration$LiquibaseDataSourceCondition` and related Spring Boot condition classes, but the fix did not converge. The generated test file and intervention summary are also worth checking: `tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-liquibase/4.1.0/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot_liquibase/Spring_boot_liquibaseTest.java` and `post-gen-interventions/org.springframework.boot_spring-boot-liquibase_4.1.0.md`.\n\nNext steps:\n1. Rewrite or remove the generated Liquibase XML tests so they do not depend on remote HTTP XSD resolution in native image.\n2. Investigate and add the missing Spring Boot native metadata for the Liquibase auto-configuration path, especially around `EnableConfigurationPropertiesRegistrar` and `LiquibaseAutoConfiguration` nested condition/configuration classes, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-liquibase:4.1.0`.\n3. Refresh the stats after the native test passes so dynamic-access coverage is available."}}
